S-task16.answer.value: It is surprising the the network has an obvious 'nucleus' of contributors and then such an array of outliers. For example Helwig only interacts with Thomas. Unsurprisingly those outliers have the fewest followers and often tweets. However looking towards the centre of the diagram - where you see the most nodes you would expect to see a correlation between tweets and follows (e.g. like Robert) but that isn't always the case. Tamara MViews and EEyes have lots of tweets but not a correspondingly high number of followers. Most users tend to be from North America or Europe - there also tend to be geographical clusters. Maybe time difference and real-time interactions still have a bearing in the digital age?It also appears institutions have fewer followers overall than people. Interesting!
